  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a single frame in an animated WebP encoding operation.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoderFrame` represents a single frame in an animated WebP sequence.
Each frame wraps a <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> and a display duration in milliseconds.

Create an instance from an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKBitmap>, an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKImage>,
or directly from an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap>. When the frame is no longer needed,
dispose of it to release any internally managed resources.

Pass a span of frames to one of the
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoder.EncodeAnimated*> overloads to produce an animated
WebP file.
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
